    "body": "### Description\n\nI've migrated my config to the new-style `vim.lsp.config()`. I previously had a catch-all `on_attach` handler that set-up various keybindings, this now looks like:\n\n```lua\nlocal capabilities = require(\"cmp_nvim_lsp\").default_capabilities()\n\nlocal function on_attach(client, bufnr)\n  require(\"my.mappings\").lsp_mapping(bufnr)\nend\n\nvim.lsp.config(\"*\", {\n  on_attach = on_attach,\n  capabilities = capabilities,\n})\n```\n\nHowever, it looks like the `on_attach` from some client configs (such as `ts_ls`) is overriding this instead of being merged with this. See https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/4bc481b6f0c0cf3671fc894debd0e00347089a4e/lsp/ts_ls.lua#L100\n\nIs this an upstream problem?\n\nRelated #3790 ",
